Large swathes of north and central Texas were hit with tornadoes and baseball-size hail Sunday night as part of a severe storm system sweeping the region .
The storm started Sunday evening in Comanche County , Texas and moved northeast towards the Dallas/Fort Worth .
More than five tornadoes were reported in the region , including a massive funnel cloud seen forming over Stephenville , 70 miles southeast of Fort Worth .
Residents were urged to stay indoors and seek shelter because of flying debris .
